parameters.text:
=Write a fresh outreach email (variation {{ $('Webhook').item.json.body._seed }}) for:
- Name: {{ $('Webhook').item.json.body.name }}
- Agency: {{ $('Webhook').item.json.body.agency_name }}
- Suburb: {{ $('Webhook').item.json.body.suburb || '' }}
{{ $('Webhook').item.json.body.custom_instructions ? 'Custom instructions: ' + $('Webhook').item.json.body.custom_instructions : '' }}

Each variation must use different wording, a different subject line, and a different angle on the pain points.

parameters.jsCode:
const text = $input.first().json.output || '';
let draft = { subject: '', body: '' };
try {
  const fenceStripped = text.replace(/```json\s*/g, '').replace(/```\s*/g, '').trim();
  const match = fenceStripped.match(/\{[\s\S]*\}/);
  if (match) draft = JSON.parse(match[0]);
} catch(e) {
  draft = { subject: 'SmartFlow intro', body: text };
}
return [{ json: draft }];

const draft = $input.first().json;
const body = $('Webhook').item.json.body;
const agency = String(body.agency_name || '').trim();
const suburb = String(body.suburb || '').trim();

const usedSubjects = new Set(
  $('Fetch Prior Subjects').all().map(item => String(item.json.subject || '').trim().toLowerCase()).filter(Boolean)
);

const subject = String(draft.subject || '').trim();
if (subject && !usedSubjects.has(subject.toLowerCase())) {
  return [{ json: draft }];
}

const locationToken = suburb || agency.split(/\s+/)[0] || 'your market';
const candidateSubjects = [
  `Are you actually responding to every enquiry?`,
  `Still following up leads by hand?`,
  `The lead you missed while at an inspection`,
  `3 hours a day on emails is too much`,
  `Most agents lose leads before lunch`,
  `What if every enquiry got a reply in under 2 minutes?`,
  `Something worth 5 minutes of your time`,
  `What I noticed about agencies in ${locationToken}`,
  `Are your competitors responding faster than you?`,
  `How much time did you spend on follow-ups today?`,
  `When does follow-up actually happen?`,
  `How many enquiries went cold this week?`,
  `The reply delay costing you inspections`,
  `A faster way to handle weekend enquiries`,
  `What happens after 5 pm at ${agency || 'your agency'}`,
  `Could every enquiry get a response in minutes?`,
  `Why good enquiries still go missing`,
  `Weekend opens should not slow replies`,
  `A better follow-up rhythm for ${agency || 'busy agents'}`,
  `Is manual follow-up still worth it?`,
  `What top agents protect with automation`,
  `How many leads are waiting right now?`,
  `Fast replies change conversion`,
  `The follow-up gap hurting busy agents`,
  `Where enquiry response time breaks down`,
  `A small fix for a costly delay`,
];

const unused = candidateSubjects.filter(candidate => !usedSubjects.has(candidate.toLowerCase()));
const replacement = unused.length > 0
  ? unused[Math.floor(Math.random() * unused.length)]
  : `${candidateSubjects[0]} ${usedSubjects.size + 1}`;

return [{ json: { ...draft, subject: replacement } }];

